Subject: [PATCH 057/129] =?UTF-8?q?config:=20deshabilitar=20RESET=5FGPIO?=
 =?UTF-8?q?=20=E2=80=94=20rompe=20mmc-pwrseq-simple=20con=20#gpio-cells=3D?=
 =?UTF-8?q?3=20(WiFi=20AP6256=20en=20mmc1)?=
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

El fallback reset-GPIO del core de reset solo soporta #gpio-cells=2
(__reset_add_reset_gpio_device devuelve -ENOENT con 3 celdas de sunxi),
y con RESET_GPIO habilitado IS_ENABLED activa esa ruta en pwrseq_simple
-> probe -2 -> mmc1 nunca prueba. Sin RESET_GPIO, pwrseq usa el camino
clasico devm_gpiod_get_array (equivalente al BSP 5.15).

Co-Authored-By: Claude Fable 5 <noreply@anthropic.com>
---
 .config | 2 +-
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+), 1 deletion(-)

diff --git a/.config b/.config
index 28091ecf1..7bd92f1a7 100644
--- a/.config
+++ b/.config
@@ -8078,7 +8078,7 @@ CONFIG_PARTITION_PERCPU=y
 # CONFIG_IPACK_BUS is not set
 CONFIG_ARCH_HAS_RESET_CONTROLLER=y
 CONFIG_RESET_CONTROLLER=y
-CONFIG_RESET_GPIO=m
+# CONFIG_RESET_GPIO is not set
 # CONFIG_RESET_MCHP_SPARX5 is not set
 CONFIG_RESET_NUVOTON_MA35D1=y
 CONFIG_RESET_SCMI=y
